Do you love working with elementary aged students? If so, we have some job opportunities. If you're interested please call Karen Roys at (810) 448-4001 or email kroys@dryden.k12.mi.us.

Parapro in our Special Education program. Monday - Friday, around 30 hours a week.

Lunch/recess aide - A couple of hours mid-day. We'd love if you're available every day of the week but will also consider candidates who need a more flexible schedule.

World Music Wednesday Challenge: Take some time today & research a little bit about movies created in Bollywood. Find one that seems interesting to you, and choose a video clip of a song from the movie. Why did this movie/song interest you?

Do you know which city makes the MOST movies in the world? For most of us living in the United States, we would automatically think of Hollywood, California, but that‚Äôs not the right answer. Mumbai, India- also known as Bollywood- produces about 1,000 movies per year. That‚Äôs 400 more than what Hollywood averages! Music takes a HUGE role in Bollywood productions. In fact, most of their movies would seem like musicals to us. Take a listen to the video below to get a taste of what this music typically sounds like! #proudcardinal #worldmusicwednesday

https://youtu.be/WiARWF73C9w

Ankle bells and Klezmer music | Kid's music | Mini Episodes | Lah-Lah

Dryden Bands and Music
May 20 at 2:49 PM ¬∑

World Music Wednesday: Find items you have around your house to make your own ankle bells. Then send me a video of you playing them!

Klezmer is a Jewish style of music that features the clarinet. It is not played in the way that you might be used to hearing it, however. Instead, they move their fingers and mouth in a way that BENDS the pitch. This technique allows them to show emotion in their music in a unique way. Take a few minutes to watch this mini-episode from the Youtube Channel, ‚ÄúLah, Lah‚Äù to learn more about Klezmer, and how to make ankle bells too!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kP1V62P0CWI

Listening to nature's music

Dryden Bands and Music
May 18 at 3:24 PM ¬∑

Motivational Monday Challenge: The best music doesn‚Äôt always come from people playing instruments or singing powerful lyrics. Many people find that listening to sounds that are created naturally in their favorite environment to be soothing, and gives their mind an opportunity to take a break. Send me a short video clip of your favorite ‚Äúnatural‚Äù music. What about it is relaxing to you?

‚ÄúIn surrounding yourself with the natural environment ‚Äî by going for walk in the forest, paddle-boarding on a lake, or sitting and reading a book in the heart of the woods ‚Äî you are allowing your body to breathe and slow down. You‚Äôre letting your mind relax, while your ears focus on the sounds around you.‚Äù
Take some time to read the article below by yourself, or with your family. There are some great ideas to find music everywhere you go!üñ§‚ù§Ô∏èüñ§‚ù§Ô∏è #motivationalmonday #proudcardinal

http://www.ontarioparks.com/parksblog/natures-music/

Motivational Monday Challenge: The best music doesn‚Äôt always come from people playing instruments or singing powerful lyrics. Many people find that listening to sounds that are created naturally in their favorite environment to be soothing, and gives their mind an opportunity to take a break. Send me a short video clip of your favorite ‚Äúnatural‚Äù music. What about it is relaxing to you?

‚ÄúIn surrounding yourself with the natural environment ‚Äî by going for walk in the forest, paddle-boarding on a lake, or sitting and reading a book in the heart of the woods ‚Äî you are allowing your body to breathe and slow down. You‚Äôre letting your mind relax, while your ears focus on the sounds around you.‚Äù
Take some time to read the article below by yourself, or with your family. There are some great ideas to find music everywhere you go!üñ§‚ù§Ô∏èüñ§‚ù§Ô∏è #motivationalmonday #proudcardinal

YOUTUBE.COM
Go-Go Beats & Variations: Drum Lesson | Stanton Moore

Dryden Bands and Music
May 15 at 1:22 PM ¬∑

Funky Friday Challenge: Find some items around your house that you could use to create a cool beat. You might choose some pots in the kitchen, boxes in the storage room, or anything else your parents are okay with you making into some drums for a quick video! Send me your creations!

Just like Funk was inspired by a variety of different styles of music, it also served as the inspiration for music that came after it! Native to Washington D.C., Go-Go music‚Äôs main purpose was to keep people on the dance floor while other musicians got ready for the next song in the set. In other words, it‚Äôs the ULTIMATE dance music! What I like most about this style is that its purpose is very similar to how Hip Hop got started (take a look at our #turntabletuesday posts for more info), but uses live instruments instead of the turntable. Pretty cool! Take a look at this short drum set lesson, where you can see how each element gets layered on top of each other to create that unique dance beat!

https://youtu.be/tg47K08_iKk

Steel Drums

Dryden Bands and Music
May 13 at 12:13 PM ¬∑

World Music Wednesday: Most steel drums learn their music by ear- or WITHOUT sheet music. Can you figure out how to play a tune without reading or writing out music for it? (You choose the instrument!) Send me a video clip!

Arguably one of the most famous instruments from the Caribbean Islands is the steel drum. If you have ever visited a tropical area, odds are you have heard one being played! Take a look at this video clip to learn more about how they work, and what they are made from:

https://youtu.be/q3rbRoOJkbQ

Gaming Music Makes You More Productive?!

Dryden Bands and Music
May 11 at 1:37 PM ¬∑

Motivational Monday Challenge: Which video game has the best music? Do you think it helps make the playing experience better? Why? Send a picture or video of you playing!

Video game creators spend years perfecting every part of the gaming experience- including the music! For example, can you hum the tune to the first level of Super Mario Brothers? What about Tetris or Pac Man? Is it possible that these are specifically included to help a gamer play at their best? Absolutely! Take a look at this video for more information!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w67jhwvDQso&feature=emb_logo

Dryden Bands and Music
May 5 at 1:28 AM ¬∑

THIS IS BEAUTIFUL!! üé∂üéµ
‚ÄúI don't know how to fully express what music means to me. Music is an incredible blessing to everyone and everything. The thing that strikes me the most about music is how it's a universal language. Music can be heard worldwide without translation, and that's part of the magic of it. It's also crazy to me that while everyone can listen to music, no matter what language you speak or the beliefs you cherish, the way an individual interprets it can be vastly different. Composers may have a story or something behind a specific song, but the magic of music allows other people to listen to it and create their own story. Music is unique, original. It helps people laugh, cry, vent, and much more. That is why music is so very special to me.‚Äù Thank you Jacob Livingston! ‚ù§Ô∏èüñ§‚ù§Ô∏èüñ§#motivationalmonday #proudcardinal

Dryden Bands and Music
May 4 at 2:15 PM ¬∑

Motivational Monday Challenge: What does music mean to you? Are you drawn to create and perform with an instrument/your voice, or are you more of a listener? Send me a picture- a selfie, or something else that represents your love for music!

‚ÄúI have to sing, I have to play. The music, it‚Äôs not just in me, it is me. When life gets me down, I play my guitar.‚Äù -Miguel from Disney‚Äôs Coco

Miguel‚Äôs family has a challenging history with music. It goes back many generations, and everyone has vowed to keep music out of their lives forever; but as much as he tries, Miguel just CAN‚ÄôT stay away. I can definitely relate to how he feels, and it is a big reason why I became music teacher! Take some time today, or whenever you can, to watch this amazing story- you will definitely not regret it! (It is available to stream on Disney+ üòÅ) #motivationalmonday #proudcardinal

I can definitely relate to how he feels, and it is a big reason why I became music teacher! Take some time today, or whenever you can, to watch this amazing story- you will definitely not regret it! (It is available to stream on Disney+ üòÅ) #motivationalmonday #proudcardinal

World Music Wednesday Challenge: Search ‚ÄúMariachi Music‚Äù on your favorite music streaming app- Spotify, Apple Music, Pandora, YouTube, etc. Listen to a few songs and choose a favorite. (If you really don‚Äôt like this type of music, choose the song you dislike the least.) Send me a link/name & artist for your song, and answer the following questions: What about this song makes you like it more than the rest that you listened to? Why do you think this music is popular?

WHAT IS MARIACHI MUSIC AND WHERE DOES IT COME FROM?? The simple answer is that it is a style of music from Mexico. These groups of musicians can vary in size, but are typically 3-20 people playing violins, trumpets, guitars, vihuela (a special Mexican guitar), and guitarron (a special Mexican bass guitar). Take a look at this video to learn more about this style of music, and hear the KAIA quartet perform one! #worldmusicwednesday #proudcardinal

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IKEDd9AQUns

Dryden Bands and Music
April 28 at 4:12 PM ¬∑

Turntable Tuesday Challenge: What is your favorite Hip Hop song? Why do you like it? (send a youtube link of the song, so others can check it out too!)

Did you know that Hip Hop was created by a Jamaican DJ named Kool Herc? It happened during a NYC Summer Block Party in 1973 that Herc (known as Clive Campbell at this time) and his sister organized to raise money to purchase necessary supplies for school. He had the idea to have two copies of the same album on his double turntable so he could extend his favorite instrumental (or non-singing) section of a popular song. What was originally planned to give his guests a special beat to dance to quickly turned into an opportunity for them to add their own rhymes! And voila- Hip Hop was born! #turntabletuesday #proudcardinal

Motivational Monday Challenge: Is there a certain song/artist/genre that you like to listen to when you want to calm your mind? Why do you think the music helps? Send a picture with your submission!

Taking some time to meditate when you‚Äôre feeling overwhelmed is a great way to practice self-care. A popular musical trend in many meditation practices is the use of singing bowls. Singing Bowls are a type of bell that produces a unique tone when played. Many people describe a deep sense of calm as they listen to the vibrations these instruments create. Take a look at this video of a singing bowl being played. The bowl has been filled with water so you can SEE the vibrations work their magic! #motivationalmonday #drydenbandsandmusic #proudcardinal

Dryden Bands and Music
April 22 at 7:33 PM ¬∑

Lily Finnigan took the #worldmusicwednesday challenge! She chose two versions of ‚ÄúSomewhere Over The Rainbow‚Äù- one from The Wizard of Oz (https://youtu.be/PSZxmZmBfnU ), and one performed by a musician named IZ (https://youtu.be/V1bFr2SWP1I ) ‚ÄúThey both use the same lyrics but the movie version is more sad. In the movie Dorothy sang the song right after getting in trouble from her aunt. Her aunt told her to find a place where she wouldn‚Äôt get in trouble and Dorothy wondered if there was such a place. In the IZ version, the song is more upbeat. To me, it is a more positive version of people having dreams and going after them,‚Äù she says. ‚ÄúI love this song and I really like both versions. To me, it is summed up in the line ‚Äòand the dreams that you dare to dream really do come true.‚Äô‚Äù #drydenbandsandmusic #proudcardinal

From Phonographs to Spotify: A Brief History of the Music Industry

Dryden Bands and Music

Turntable Tuesday Challenge: Let‚Äôs start preparing for our future DJ careers! First step- make an awesome playlist. üòé Save the BLANK Cassette Tape Playlist Worksheet in the comments of this post and fill it out with your top 8 song choices. You can print it out and write them in, or add text electronically- then submit it! Mrs. Klann‚Äôs choices will be posted in the comments as well if you need an example. üéµüé∂

So far, we have learned that the turntable was originally a vital part of the phonograph/record player- the cutting edge technology of music playing in the late 1800‚Äôs/early 1900‚Äôs. By the 1970‚Äôs individuals called Disc Jockey‚Äôs (DJ‚Äôs for short) were beginning to discover that these devices could actually be used as instruments in performance. How has this turned into the electronic music we have today? It all starts with our music playing technology! Watch this video to learn more about how our music-listening technology has evolved over the past 100 years or so! ‚ù§Ô∏èüñ§‚ù§Ô∏èüñ§ #turntabletuesday #drydenbandsandmusic #proudcardinal

post_text:
Food Service Update - We will continue to distribute breakfasts and lunches like we have been - from 8-10am on Mondays and Thursdays - through the end of the scheduled school year, June 12.

We would like to be able to offer the Summer Food Service Program but we don't currently qualify to do that. We need a certain percentage of students to qualify for free or reduced lunch and we are very close, but not quite there. If your financial circumstances have changed since the beginning of the school year and you don't already qualify for free/reduced lunch, we are asking that you complete the online application form so we can qualify for the Summer Food Service Program. It really is a matter of about 10 more students we need to qualify for free/reduced lunch and we will qualify for the Summer Food Service Program. Thank you for your help.
https://www.lunchapp.com/
